Welcome to timtaps.com

Website for Tim J Hickey 

Tim J Hickey (TimTaps) began acting at age twenty-one, then took up tap dancing at the age of twenty-four after seeing 42nd Street on Broadway and being inspired by Jerry Orbach. He studied dance in Boston, MA at Gold Studios with Rhee and Rennie Gold, then with their mother Sherry, who suggested to him the moniker “Tim Taps”.  He continued studying rhythm-tap with Jimmy “Sir Slyde” Mitchell at Leon Collins' Tappers Paradise, and swing and acrobatic jitterbug with Bob E. Thomas. Tim then began working as a professional entertainer soon after.
